/VonNeumann.html#ZFSet.vonNeumann\">vonNeumann</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/VonNeumann.html#ZFSet.mem_vonNeumann'","kind":"theorem","line":48,"name":"ZFSet.mem_vonNeumann'","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/VonNeumann.lean#L48-L48"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/VonNeumann.html#ZFSet.termV_\"><span class=\"name\">ZFSet</span>.<span class=\"name\">termV_</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The von Neumann hierarchy is defined so that `V_ o` is the union of the powersets of all\n`V_ a` for `a < o`. It satisfies the following properties:\n\n- `vonNeumann_zero`: `V_ 0 = ∅`\n- `vonNeumann_succ`: `V_ (succ a) = powerset (V_ a)`\n- `vonNeumann_of_isSuccPrelimit`: `IsSuccPrelimit a → V_ a = ⋃ b < a, V_ b`\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/VonNeumann.html#ZFSet.termV_","kind":"def","line":43,"name":"ZFSet.termV_","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/VonNeumann.lean#L43-L44"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/VonNeumann.html#ZFSet.vonNeumann\"><span class=\"name\">ZFSet</span>.<span class=\"name\">vonNeumann</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">o</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/Ordinal/Basic.html#Ordinal\">Ordinal.{u}</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/Basic.html#ZFSet\">ZFSet.{u}</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The von Neumann hierarchy is defined so that `V_ o` is the union of the powersets of all\n`V_ a` for `a < o`. It satisfies the following properties:\n\n- `vonNeumann_zero`: `V_ 0 = ∅`\n- `vonNeumann_succ`: `V_ (succ a) = powerset (V_ a)`\n- `vonNeumann_of_isSuccPrelimit`: `IsSuccPrelimit a → V_ a = ⋃ b < a, V_ b`\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/VonNeumann.html#ZFSet.vonNeumann","kind":"def","line":31,"name":"ZFSet.vonNeumann","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/SetTheory/ZFC/VonNeumann.lean#L31-L41"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.SetTheory.Cardinal.Arithmetic","Mathlib.SetTheory.ZFC.Class"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.SetTheory.ZFC.VonNeumann"}